The 2006-07 Palau Soccer League was the fourth season of association football competition in Palau and the first to straddle two calendar years.[1] The league was won by Team Bangladesh,[2] their second title.[1]Five teams will compete in the 2006-07 season of the Palau Soccer League. All matches will played at the PCC Track & Field Stadium in Koror, home stadium to all the teams. This is due to the lack of suitable venues for soccer matches in Palau. The teams for 2006-07 (listed in alphabetical order) are:The location of the PCC Track & Field Stadium, where all games will take place:Updated to games played on 4 Nov 2011.
